83rd OREGON LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY--2026 Regular Session
House Bill 4094
Sponsored by Representative NELSON, Senators MANNING JR, GORSEK, Representatives CHAICHI, CHOTZEN,
RIEKE SMITH, WISE, Senator CAMPOS; Representatives ANDERSEN, GAMBA, ISADORE, MUNOZ, SOSA,
TRAN, WALTERS, Senators FREDERICK, NERON MISSLIN, PATTERSON (Presession filed.)
SUMMARY
The following summary is not prepared by the sponsors of the measure and is not a part of the body thereof subject
to consideration by the Legislative Assembly. It is an editor’s brief statement of the essential features of the
measure as introduced. The statement includes a measure digest written in compliance with applicable readability
standards.
Digest: This Act makes laws about payouts for certain unused paid time off. (Flesch Readability
Score: 81.8).
Requires employers who provide paid vacation time to compensate employees for all earned or
accrued but unused paid vacation time when employment terminates.
Takes effect on the 91st day following adjournment sine die.
1 A BILL FOR AN ACT
2 Relating to compensation for certain unused paid time off upon termination of employment; creating
3 new provisions; amending ORS 652.140; and prescribing an effective date.
4 Be It Enacted by the People of the State of Oregon:
5 SECTION 1. (1) As used in this section:
6 (a) “Paid vacation time” means an employer-provided benefit allowing employees to take
7 time off from work without loss of pay for vacation leave.
8 (b) “Paid vacation time” does not mean an employer-provided benefit allowing employees
9 to take time off from work without loss of pay for:
10 (A) Sick time governed by ORS 653.601 to 653.661, or any other leave that is designated
11 for, may be used for or is taken for illness or other health-related purposes, including any
12 portion of an employer-provided benefit designated to meet the minimum requirements of
13 ORS 653.601 to 653.661.
14 (B) Personal business leave.
15 (C) Holidays and floating holidays.
16 (2) If an employer provides employees with paid vacation time pursuant to an employer
17 policy or otherwise, the employer shall, upon the termination of the employment relation-
18 ship, compensate the employee, at one hundred percent of the employee’s regular rate of pay
19 for all earned or accrued but unused paid vacation time, in accordance with the manner and
20 timeframe set forth under ORS 652.140 for the payment of final wages.
21 (3) Nothing in this section prohibits an employer from adopting a written policy or en-
22 tering into an employment contract that:
23 (a) Establishes the method or rate of earning or accrual of paid vacation time;
24 (b) Establishes requirements for requesting and scheduling paid vacation time; or
25 (c) Requires employees to use earned or accrued paid vacation time by a specific date or
26 that provides for the forfeiture of unused paid vacation time not used by that date, provided
27 that:
28 (A) The employer provides employees with written notice of such requirement at the time
